1
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,367
Any updates on Jeff's case?

2
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,500
From the video Colonel Sarabia
sent, a white van pulls up.

3
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:22,633
Then, when it drives off,

4
00:00:22,767 --> 00:00:23,967
Jeffrey's gone, too.

5
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:27,500
What's strange is,
it's been days.

6
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:29,467
No ransom demand.

7
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,100
Unless they have another motive.

8
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:36,567
How are you, Jeff?

9
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,100
Still holding up?

10
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,200
Hazel.

11
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,900
Let me out!
Why did you bring me here?

12
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:47,200
Let me go!

13
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:48,567
You animal!

14
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:49,433
Monster!

15
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:52,233
If you don't believe me anymore,

16
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:53,867
I'll get revenge
for my child myself.

17
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,200
Hazel,

18
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:57,100
all I want is...

19
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:01,267
the truth about Jessica.

20
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:06,167
Maybe our anger and need
for revenge have gone too far.

21
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,000
Maybe their family
isn't that bad.

22
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:10,233
Just admit it.
You're scared.

23
00:01:14,567 --> 00:01:15,967
Who is Hazel with?

24
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:22,033
You jerk, Hazel!
That's my phone!

25
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:24,700
What's that?

26
00:01:25,167 --> 00:01:26,567
Give it back!

27
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,000
It's mine!

28
00:01:28,133 --> 00:01:28,800
Give it back!

29
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:30,767
Smile!

30
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,233
Look at this.

31
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:37,067
I hope you die!

32
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:39,300
The pleasure is mine!

33
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:44,600
My shot is so great.

34
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:45,433
- Bye!
- How long are we going

35
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:46,533
to torture that guy?

36
00:01:46,667 --> 00:01:48,733
Why don't we ask
for ransom already?

37
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:53,433
What?

38
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,300
Let's be clear.

39
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,667
I'm not doing this for money.

40
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,933
We are.

41
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:07,833
In addition to what you pay us,
we want to earn more.

42
00:02:08,733 --> 00:02:10,400
So let's ask for a ransom.

43
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,167
Don't act as if you know better.

44
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,633
Don't get ahead of my plan.

45
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:18,300
You do exactly what I say.
You got it?

46
00:02:19,433 --> 00:02:20,767
Get it together!

47
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:27,767
Let me out of here!

48
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,067
Here you go, Sir.

49
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,933
If you need anything,
just call me.

50
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:42,300
Thank you so much, Didang.

51
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,467
Thanks.

52
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:49,767
Lance is still in jail.

53
00:02:50,033 --> 00:02:51,133
He strongly denies

54
00:02:51,267 --> 00:02:54,333
having anything to do
with Jeffrey's disappearance.

55
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:56,133
Even Colonel Sarabia.

56
00:02:57,167 --> 00:03:00,300
And the private investigator
I hired

57
00:03:00,433 --> 00:03:04,267
can't trace the van seen
on the airport CCTV.

58
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:10,533
If that van was used
in the kidnapping,

59
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:12,400
then whoever did this is a pro.

60
00:03:13,967 --> 00:03:16,700
What if we change strategies?

61
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,500
What do you mean?

62
00:03:19,633 --> 00:03:22,333
Felma and I have a strong
feeling

63
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,100
that Hazel is involved in what's
happening to our kids.

64
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,267
I'm thinking...

65
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:34,467
we let Colonel Sarabia track
the van.

66
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:39,000
Then the private investigator
focuses on Hazel.

67
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,367
You mean...

68
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,700
put Hazel under surveillance?

69
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:44,367
Yeah.

70
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:47,633
She might be the one
who can lead us to Jeffrey.

71
00:03:57,033 --> 00:03:58,733
Your instincts were right.

72
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:02,433
Hazel is connected to the man
who chased you.

73
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:06,133
You know, Sis, I really feel it.

74
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:11,200
It felt different when I saw
them talking at the cemetery.

75
00:04:12,933 --> 00:04:16,900
We just need one solid piece
of evidence, Coleen.

76
00:04:17,033 --> 00:04:22,933
To connect Hazel to everything
that's happening to our family.

77
00:04:23,067 --> 00:04:24,833
She'd better watch out.

78
00:04:24,967 --> 00:04:27,167
So just stay focused
on following her, Sis.

79
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,267
Do you think
she noticed us?

80
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:37,433
We've been tailing
her for a while now.

81
00:05:37,567 --> 00:05:39,400
She ate,
did some grocery shopping...

82
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,633
I don't think so.

83
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:44,967
Wait, looks like she's leaving.
Let's go.

84
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:04,800
Where did she go?

85
00:06:04,933 --> 00:06:06,800
She disappeared fast.

86
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:08,400
Are you looking for me?

87
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:15,667
Are you stalking me?

88
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:18,600
Guard!

89
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,200
Guard!

90
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:23,133
Us? Stalking?

91
00:06:23,267 --> 00:06:26,267
Why are you here?
You're following us again?

92
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,733
Hey, I've caught you.

93
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:29,433
Don't even try to deny it!

94
00:06:29,567 --> 00:06:32,500
- Guard!
- Can you not make a scene?

95
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:33,833
Why not?

96
00:06:33,967 --> 00:06:35,467
I caught you red-handed.

97
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:37,233
So stop pretending!

98
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:39,467
Guard!

99
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:42,000
Fine, call the guards! Guard!

100
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:43,167
- Guard!
- Guard!

101
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:47,700
You really think
you can fool me, huh?

102
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,700
I've noticed you're tailing me
for a while now.

103
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,567
I just didn't let it show.

104
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,467
All those lame disguises.

105
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:56,467
You think I wouldn't recognize
you? You look ridiculous.

106
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:59,733
Next time you step
intomy territory,

107
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:01,233
do your homework first.

108
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:04,267
Your territory?

109
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,100
You hear that, Sir?

110
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:09,300
Turns out she owns
this mall now.

111
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,000
Wow, someone's full of herself.

112
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:13,833
You really think
we're following you?

113
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,900
We came here to shop and park.

114
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:17,433
I literally just parked.

115
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:19,967
Oh, please.
Stop lying.

116
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:21,233
You know what, Sir?

117
00:07:21,367 --> 00:07:23,133
I've already filed a blotter
report against these two

118
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:24,400
for assault before.

119
00:07:24,533 --> 00:07:27,500
So I'm sure they're after me.
They're planning something.

120
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:29,667
Sir, please don't believe her.

121
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:32,000
My sister and I
are just here to shop.

122
00:07:32,133 --> 00:07:33,533
We even have a car.

123
00:07:33,667 --> 00:07:36,533
And we were going to park.

124
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:39,133
You really think
you're the main character.

125
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:41,900
You're seriously delusional.

126
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:44,600
You're making up stories
like it's nothing.

127
00:07:44,733 --> 00:07:45,833
If I were you, Sir,

128
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:49,267
I'd detain these two in the
security office. Now. Do it.

129
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:53,600
As I said earlier, Sir,
she doesn't own this mall.

130
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:56,433
Then why is she stopping us
from coming in?

131
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:59,967
You know what? Come on, Coleen.
Let's just go.

132
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:01,933
I'm so annoyed with
this delusional woman.

133
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:05,067
Wait. What do you mean, go?

134
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:06,567
Where do you think
you're going?

135
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:08,433
Sir, what are you waiting for?
Arrest them!

136
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:11,533
Ma'am, I'm sorry,
but they're customers, too.

137
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:14,500
And they didn't approach
you to hurt you.

138
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:16,367
You're the one who approached
them, right?

139
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:17,567
I'm sorry.

140
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,567
Let's go.

141
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:37,533
Next time, don't act on impulse.

142
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:40,300
You were lucky
you got out of that.

143
00:08:40,433 --> 00:08:42,700
What if you were
detained at the mall?

144
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:46,367
What if Hazel had you arrested?

145
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:50,100
Mom, we didn't approach her
first.

146
00:08:50,233 --> 00:08:54,133
She's the one
who confronted us first.

147
00:08:55,733 --> 00:08:58,967
No. You should've told us
what happened at the cemetery

148
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,867
so we could've handled it.

149
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,333
You could've gotten hurt.

150
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:04,400
We already got dragged
to the village hall.

151
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,367
Sorry, Dad.

152
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:12,767
We just wanted to help get
justice for our family.

153
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:15,767
You know,

154
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:18,333
Manuel and I
even thought about...

155
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:22,633
having Hazel followed
by a private investigator.

156
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:25,533
But we have to wait
and trust the process.

157
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:28,033
I can't wait any longer.

158
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,100
I can't.

159
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:33,467
- We already lost Joel.
- Don't say that, dear.

160
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:37,300
Nothing bad will happen
to your brother.

161
00:09:38,767 --> 00:09:41,400
- How can you be so sure, Mom?
- I said stop already.

162
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:45,267
We will find your brother.

163
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,467
But when? When?

164
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,633
Enough!

165
00:09:49,867 --> 00:09:52,900
What good will fighting do?

166
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,367
Can we all calm down?

167
00:09:56,067 --> 00:09:59,100
Let's not get overwhelmed.

168
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:01,600
We need to control
the situation.

169
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:08,000
Let's just pray.

170
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:10,067
Let's ask God for guidance.

171
00:10:11,367 --> 00:10:13,233
I'm sorry, Mom.

172
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:14,333
I'm sorry.

173
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:19,033
But I can't pray right now.

174
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:23,533
Everything that's happening
to our family hurts too much.

175
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:25,667
Andrea!

176
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,667
Don't talk like that!

177
00:10:39,133 --> 00:10:40,900
Okay. Thanks.

178
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:42,033
Bye.

179
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:45,767
That was
the private investigator.

180
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:49,167
He's following Hazel.

181
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:51,967
She's riding in a car.

182
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:57,567
I hope she leads him
to where Jeffrey is.

183
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,033
My god.

184
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,167
Please keep our eldest safe.

185
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,333
Come on. Get inside.

186
00:11:21,533 --> 00:11:22,900
Good thing he's asleep.

187
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,567
Hey, man, fix the blindfold.

188
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,167
Behave!

189
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,300
That's good.

190
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:42,167
You know, we can make money off
this idiot.

191
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:43,700
Big money.

192
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:49,633
Maybe you can talk to Madame
Hazel when she gets here later?

193
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:51,667
Let's just ask for a ransom.

194
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,067
Yeah, boss.

195
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:57,567
You animal!

196
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:59,500
You still wanna fight back?

197
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,567
Darn that blindfold!

198
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:06,067
Fix it already!

199
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:14,867
Nando,

200
00:12:15,033 --> 00:12:17,333
go buy us some beer outside.

201
00:12:17,467 --> 00:12:19,700
To...

202
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:20,700
cool off a bit.

203
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,367
Come on, man.

204
00:12:23,467 --> 00:12:25,067
- Go already.
- Yeah, sure.

205
00:12:26,967 --> 00:12:29,233
- Buy a lot.
- I'll handle things here.

206
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:34,467
Traitor!

207
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,800
You animal!

208
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,100
Monster!

209
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:40,733
- Jeffrey! Jeffrey! Jeffrey!
- Let go of me!

210
00:12:40,867 --> 00:12:43,633
Listen to me. Listen. Listen.

211
00:12:43,767 --> 00:12:47,000
I won't hurt you. Don't waste
your strength. You understand?

212
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:56,733
Come on.

213
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:00,933
Jeffrey!

214
00:13:01,067 --> 00:13:02,400
Wait, listen to me!

215
00:13:02,533 --> 00:13:04,433
I won't hurt you.

216
00:13:09,133 --> 00:13:11,667
What do you think is happening
to Dad now?

217
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,067
Just keep praying, Tetay, okay?

218
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,667
God knows...

219
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,967
where Jeffrey is.

220
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:20,433
He'll save your father.

221
00:13:20,567 --> 00:13:21,900
Yes, Pretty Mama.

222
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:24,700
Hush now, sweetheart.

223
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:28,833
Aunt Felma, Uncle Manuel,

224
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:33,500
please message us right away
if there's any update.

225
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:35,733
You can count on it.

226
00:13:35,867 --> 00:13:40,933
Bye, Pretty Mama, Handsome
Papa, Aunties, bye-bye.

227
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,400
Bye.

228
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,767
Bye.

229
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,600
Dad...

230
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:59,500
Uncle Noah, any news
from your private investigator?

231
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:03,133
Is there any clue
where my brother is?

232
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:04,667
Not yet, Andrea.

233
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:40,300
This is so hard, Manuel.

234
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:44,867
I want to
reassure our kids.

235
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:49,833
Tell them Jeffrey's okay,
that we'll find him.

236
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:51,800
But...

237
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:55,500
I need reassurance, too.

238
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:58,133
We do, Felma.

239
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:00,933
We both do.

240
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:07,500
At least we're facing
this together.

241
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:09,900
Let's draw strength
from each other.

242
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:14,567
Felma, the police
are doing their job.

243
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,300
And I'm sure...

244
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:19,867
God won't abandon
our eldest son.

245
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,800
We trusted you, and you're
working with Hazel?

246
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:39,833
And this is what you do!

247
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:42,333
Jeffrey, listen to me!

248
00:15:42,467 --> 00:15:43,367
I'm getting you out of here!

249
00:15:43,633 --> 00:15:45,433
Do you understand?
I'll explain later!

250
00:15:45,567 --> 00:15:47,300
Listen to me!

251
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:52,067
- Jeffrey!
- Why should I trust you?

252
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:53,700
You're a traitor, aren't you?

253
00:15:53,933 --> 00:15:56,567
Do you want to escape or not?
They're coming back!

254
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,633
Listen to me!

255
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:01,133
I know a way out.

256
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,467
Come on. Follow me. Hurry!

257
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:06,200
This way!

258
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:10,367
Come on!

259
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:12,400
Hurry!

260
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,033
Move!

261
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,433
There you go.

262
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:29,933
Hey, do we have
any snacks?

263
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:31,900
All I got was crackers.

264
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:33,233
That's fine. That works.

265
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,300
What was that? Check it out!

266
00:17:29,767 --> 00:17:31,300
Happy hour's early today.

267
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:33,767
Who's watching Jeffrey?

268
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:35,267
Look at your men.

269
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:08,267
Where's Jeffrey?

270
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,467
Where is Jeffrey?

271
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,967
What is this? Did he escape?

272
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:22,333
You idiots! You're all idiots!

273
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:24,767
There are two of you!
You're huge!

274
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:26,133
Bastard!

275
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:44,400
It was Jojo!

276
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,400
He helped him escape!

277
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:48,267
He made us go!

278
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,267
And then helped Jeffrey!

279
00:18:51,367 --> 00:18:52,633
That bastard!

280
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:56,800
You animal, Jojo! You traitor!

281
00:19:15,667 --> 00:19:16,967
- Come on.
- Don't touch me.

282
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:19,567
- Come on.
- I said don't touch me!

283
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:34,867
Jeff!

284
00:19:41,033 --> 00:19:41,967
You jerk.

285
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:45,367
Just because you're helping me

286
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:47,333
doesn't mean I've already
forgotten you betrayed us.

287
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:51,500
I'm sorry, Jeff.

288
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:55,833
We let you into our home.

289
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:58,233
We trusted you.

290
00:19:58,367 --> 00:20:00,500
We treated you like family.

291
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:02,767
And you were spying for Hazel?

292
00:20:03,067 --> 00:20:03,933
Why? What were you doing?

293
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,733
You reported to her
everything you saw?

294
00:20:05,867 --> 00:20:07,333
Everything you heard?

295
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:08,900
Jeffrey...

296
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:10,833
I didn't know
it would end like this.

297
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,267
Please believe me.

298
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:14,633
Why did you do it?

299
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,467
For the money?

300
00:20:18,767 --> 00:20:19,433
No.

301
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:20,833
Then what?

302
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,967
Why did you side
with that devil?

303
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,200
Don't touch me!

304
00:20:49,633 --> 00:20:51,000
Why?

305
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:52,900
Why did he let
that bastard escape?

306
00:20:53,033 --> 00:20:54,900
What is this?
Are they working together now?

307
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,967
He's going to run to Felma!

308
00:20:58,533 --> 00:21:00,367
Find them now!

309
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,067
Move! Move faster!

310
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:06,767
They'll go to the police.

311
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:09,067
We have to stop this, Hazel.

312
00:21:09,233 --> 00:21:11,033
I don't want to be dragged
into this! You promised me!

313
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:13,433
You won't go to jail.
No one's going to jail.

314
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,033
I'll handle it!

315
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,933
That illegitimate family
will not win.

316
00:21:32,533 --> 00:21:33,767
Bro, thank you.

317
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:37,133
You don't owe me thanks.

318
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,233
I'm just fixing my mistakes.

319
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:49,967
Is that Hazel?

320
00:21:53,733 --> 00:21:56,600
Jeffrey, I need to deal
with her first.

321
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:59,033
You explain everything
to your parents.

322
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:01,367
Hazel might try
something again.

323
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,200
Bro, you could get hurt.

324
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:05,467
We'll be in more danger

325
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,400
if I don't fix what I started.

326
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:11,433
Jeffrey,

327
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:13,333
I hope you can forgive me.

328
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:22,433
Well, thank you
for informing me.

329
00:22:22,667 --> 00:22:23,867
Okay, thanks.

330
00:22:25,667 --> 00:22:27,667
That was
the private investigator.

331
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:28,900
What did he say?

332
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:31,333
Did he find where Jeffrey is?

333
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:33,200
Yes.

334
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,633
But he's not
there anymore.

335
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:36,667
My god.

336
00:22:38,933 --> 00:22:40,800
Where is my son?

337
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:51,367
Thank you.

338
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:53,067
Take care, bro.

339
00:23:12,233 --> 00:23:13,867
- Jeff!
- Jeffrey!

340
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,833
Jeffrey, my son.

341
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:17,367
What happened?

342
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,300
Son, what happened to you?

343
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:27,400
Bro...

344
00:23:29,767 --> 00:23:31,400
Jeff, what happened to you?

345
00:23:33,233 --> 00:23:34,100
Jeff, tell us.

346
00:23:35,467 --> 00:23:37,867
It's Hazel. Hazel did this
to you, didn't she?

347
00:23:43,433 --> 00:23:45,100
I'm not letting you
fool me anymore.

348
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:46,533
This ends now.

349
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:47,533
I'm done.

350
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:48,967
I won't back down.

351
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:53,200
Just surrender already.

352
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,300
You monster!

353
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:56,267
You really brought
the cops here?

354
00:23:56,433 --> 00:23:57,567
Enough! Stop it!

355
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:59,800
I never thought Hazel
was capable of this.

356
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:01,800
Why did Joel have to
get dragged into it?

357
00:24:02,067 --> 00:24:04,100
Joel found out
about her connection

358
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:05,967
to the man she was talking to.

359
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:07,400
It was Jojo.

360
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:09,333
Hazel is his accomplice.

361
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:11,767
I'm sorry for everything
that happened.

362
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:15,900
So you admit you conspired
with Hazel?

363
00:24:17,667 --> 00:24:18,500
You animal!

364
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:21,733
- Manuel!
- You animal!

365
00:24:21,867 --> 00:24:23,033
Wait!
